The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | India tops buyers list for Burj
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      India tops buyers list for Burj
  - businessmen own tallest tower                              The Burj in Dubai                                  
	Dubai, Dec. 1 (PTI): Indians top the list of buyers in the worlds tallest tower, having acquired space worth $7.9 million in the first seven months of the skyscrapers opening.        
	Prominent buyers of swanky apartments in Burj Khalifa tower include London-based NRI businessman Raj Kundra. He has presented an apartment to his wife Shilpa Shetty.         
	Local businessman of Indian origin B.R. Shetty, the managing director and CEO of the New Medical Centre Group of Companies in Abu Dhabi, has also bought the entire 100th floor in the tower.         
	Rizwan Sajan, the chairperson of Danube Group is also reported to have recently purchased an apartment in the tower.         
	As the world still reels under an economic downturn, the local UAE nationals come second in the list of buyers, having spent $2.62 million on buying space in the tower, a news report citing real estate information company Reidin.com has said.         
	Other major buyers include Australians, who have invested $1.25 million; Omanese, $1.14 million; Chinese, $0.62 million and Iranians, $0.73 million.         
	According to Reidin.com, the figures are based on the actual transactions registered with the land department of Dubai. Burj Khalifa has 900 studios, one, two, three and four bedroom units, while the exclusive Armani residences has 144 fully furnished private apartments.         
	The Burj offers luxurious recreational and leisure facilities, including four swimming pools, an exclusive residents lounge, health and wellness clinics.         
	The tower also boasts of the worlds highest fine-dining restaurants on the 122nd floor and at the top. It has the worlds highest observatory deck with an outdoor terrace on Level 124.                                                                                                                                                          
